node.text: When you’re in Long Beach and in need of something sweet and delicious, look no further than @pietrisbakery and this HUUUUGE stack of Baklava pancakes with powdered sugar, syrup and Nutella. They have a loaded coffee bar so you’ll have options when it comes to what to pair with this epic stack! ☕️ Pietris Bakery is not a new establishment looking to gain fans either. Apparently they’re all over Greece, and consider themselves like “The Greek Porto’s” – their words. Can’t confirm that but can confirm that these pancakes were bomb.com! Definite must-get for brunch now that dine-in is reopening! Would you try these pancakes?! Like, comment or tag a friend who would love these pancakes! ✌️😎🥞 #LAFoodieGuy #LAFG

node.text: @birrieria.gmz is having their Grand Opening tomorrow in Hawthorne outside King Henry Pub, where in addition to slangin’ delicious, crispy birria pizzas like the one above – trust, it’s bomb – they’re going to have 4 FREE soft tacos to the first 30 ppl in line starting from 9AM until 4PM! 👊 But, if you’re more of a tacos dorados type of person, they’ll have those, too! Make sure to add @birrieria.gmz spicy chili oil, too! Like, comment or tag a friend who would love some FREE tacos tomorrow! ✌️😎🐄🌮🍕 #LAFoodieGuy #LAFG

@berrybowl has been open for many years and it’s not a coincidence when you can serve healthy food at top quality in a creative way. Berry B. Does a great job and amid their selection of goodies your bound to create something that suits your fancy but if you feel overwhelmed they have a menu from smoothies to specialty bowls they can make for you right there! Like the Pitaya, Nutella, Tropical or Matcha bowls.🍵 You could even get a flight and sample multiple smaller size bowls. Berry bowl is delicious and when we say we could have this every morning to ease the stomach into the day, were not messin’ with you, it’s that tasty and refreshing. 👏 Berry Bowl is lucky to call coveted Highland Park home. Make sure to start you day here before you venture down York Blvd for the rest of the afternoon/evening. node.text:
Have you ever heard of Tejuino before? Tejuino is a cold beverage made from fermented corn and popularly consumed in the Mexican state of Jalisco and Chihuahua. (Wiki) The drink is typically thick in consistency and we’ve seen it garnished in a variety of ways. This one was pretty darn good but tejuino is usually a too thick for our pallet. And though it would make it a different drink, our touch would be adding some club soda, gingerale or sprite to make it a little more crisper with the carbonation. And maybe some tequila if we wanna get loose. 🕺Our favorite part is that they set up outside @churrosdonabel right on Whittier Blvd., which, if you haven’t been to Whittier Blvd., is a whole vibe. Make sure you hit it up the little strip of trucks and vendors if you never have. 👍 Like, comment or tag a friend who would love this! ✌️😎🍹🌽#LAFoodieGuy #LAFG ⠀⠀⠀⠀ ⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀ ⠀⠀⠀⠀ ⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀ ⠀⠀⠀⠀ ⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀ ⠀⠀⠀⠀ ⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀ ⠀⠀⠀⠀ ⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀

Blue’s Famous Rolled Tacos § Blue Horchata || Blue Burro (@bluebur.ro) || Long Beach, CA

Video Credit 🎥: @lafoodieguy 

Blue Burro models itself after those order-from-the-counter San Diego style taco spots like Mike’s Taco Club and @bluebur.ro’s delicious flavor and prime quality will have you feeling like you’re chillin’ on Newport Ave. in Ocean Beach with a shrimp and steak burrito. 🔥 But you down have to travel three hours south because it’s right here in Long Beach! 😢👏 Blue Burro even has that iconic red cream sauce that I’ve only ever seen from restaurants in SD. IYKYK. This place is bomb.com, no joke I would go here every weekend if there was one closer. The rolled tacos are perfect, the regular burritos and fries – amazing. Run here, and where you’re there tell them to open more. Thanks. Birria Queso Fundido || Cilantro Lime (@cilantrolimedtla) || Downtown LA, CA

Video Credit 🎥: @lafoodieguy 

There’s never a wrong time for some beefy, melted cheesy goodness so enter the Queso Fundido from @cilantrolimedtla nestled in a little food court in the Fashion District.🧥🪡 Best as a shareable but eat it as above by stuffing it in a tortilla and then topping it with onion, cilantro and Some salsa. A few years ago, the chef-owner started offering his family recipes up and the rest has been history. If you’re not getting this, grab their fried flautas stuffed with homemade chicken tinga and sharp cheddar. And if you’re a fan of spiciness, put their Cry Baby sauce on everything. It’s habanero salsa, FYI. 🥵 Have you been to Cilantro Lime?! ✌️😎🧀🍖 #LAFoodieGuy #LAFG

Housemade Hickory Sauce, Lettuce, Pickle, Mayo § Cheddar Cheese Burger || The Apple Pan || Los Angeles, CA

Video Cedit 🎥: @lafoodieguy 

The Apple Pan is a delicious burger 100 percent of the time that doesn’t try to do too much. Just a simple burger that’s been killin’ it on the west side for decades now! Might even be up there as one of the best in LA. 🥇 Chances are if you, your parents or your parents’ parents went to UCLA, they have heard of or been to the iconic Apple Pan! Two types of burgers, fries, tuna melt, grilled cheese and homemade pies is the whole menu and it couldn’t be better. 🔥 Even if you’re one of those types that doesn’t get Mayo on the burger like me, you get it on this burger and don’t mind it. Make sure to ask for extra Hickory sauce on the side for the fries or burger. Don’t forget the homemade pies with homemade fillings, crust and even homemade ice cream for pie a la mode. 🥧🍦Can’t wait until the U-shaped bar comes back so we can sit inside and get our sodas in the cones again. Video Credit 🎥: @adventuresofafatguy 

Biscuits and gravy done right from scratch (at least the gravy) but still stunning none the less and you know you want to take a bite! 👅 Don’t watch this in the morning because it might cause you to try to make this yourself or scramble out of the house to find a restaurant that will whip up some for you! This is definitely one of those meals the morning after a night out to soak up whatever alcohol is in your stomach. Where’s your go-to biscuits and gravy spot in LA?? Chili Cheese Fries || Pit Burger || Gardena, CA

Video Credit 🎥: @lafoodieguy 

HAPPY NATIONAL FRENCH FRY DAY, FOOD FAM!!! 🍟 From an LA landmark, Pit Burger, of all places! Pit Burger is one of those classic Angeleno spots that has been around for decades that your parents probably took you to when you were growing up. It’s one of those IYKYK places and now you know! From delicious chili fries like the above, to their famous Teriyaki Burger that will get its own feature here at some point – this is one iconic spot you will want to stop at. I always add ketchup to chili burgers-fries-dogs because the sweetness contrasts well with the savory-spicy chili. 🍅 Make sure to bring cash ‘cause it’s cash only! Have you been to Pit Burger?! Like, comment or tag a friend who should go here. ✌️😎🍔 #LAFoodieGuy #LAFG
